1
00:00:10,208 --> 00:00:13,083
I've had enough!
Leaks in Red Hook, leaks in City Hall.

2
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:15,750
-You need to find them, Buck.
-[men grunting]

3
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:17,125
Plug them.

4
00:00:17,583 --> 00:00:18,708
[gun fires]

5
00:00:19,875 --> 00:00:22,917
Whoever is leaking to the
City Without Fear site must be punished.

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,750
Find out who it is, turn them over to me.

7
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:27,875
[BB] It's my inside guy,
only he doesn't know it.

8
00:00:27,958 --> 00:00:30,708
[Daniel] If you are leaking stuff,
anything, stop.

9
00:00:30,792 --> 00:00:32,000
We could get hurt.

10
00:00:32,417 --> 00:00:35,083
[Karen] Vanessa killed Foggy
and nothing happened.

11
00:00:35,167 --> 00:00:36,542
[Matt] A line was crossed.

12
00:00:38,583 --> 00:00:41,083
Ever since Foggy died,
I didn't know who I was anymore.

13
00:00:41,167 --> 00:00:42,375
[Dex] What I did,

14
00:00:42,458 --> 00:00:44,333
what that woman had me do,

15
00:00:44,417 --> 00:00:46,083
I had to get my mind back.

16
00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:48,542
-One good deed.
-[men groan]

17
00:00:48,625 --> 00:00:50,833
-[Dex] It levels the scales again.
-[people screaming]

18
00:00:51,333 --> 00:00:53,375
[Daredevil grunts]

19
00:00:56,125 --> 00:00:57,833
[Vanessa] Wilson...

20
00:00:59,875 --> 00:01:01,792
[Fisk] Vanessa!

21
00:01:02,708 --> 00:01:04,500
[Vanessa breathing heavily]

22
00:01:11,125 --> 00:01:12,875
[♪ theme music playing]

23
00:02:59,708 --> 00:03:00,875
[waves lapping gently]

24
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:04,417
[medical machines beeping]

25
00:03:11,625 --> 00:03:13,750
[doctor] I need blood pressure.
I need heart rate stat.

26
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:15,250
-[Fisk] What's happening?
-Heart rate--

27
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:16,375
-[Fisk] No, no, no.
-Sir, sir,

28
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:18,167
-you cannot be in here right now.
-Get her!

29
00:03:18,250 --> 00:03:20,583
-Sir, you cannot be here.
-Vanessa. What is happening here?

30
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:22,375
-Sir, sir.
-Vanessa!

31
00:03:23,375 --> 00:03:24,375
Vanessa...

32
00:03:26,583 --> 00:03:28,750
-[doctor] Sir, sir. Get back.
-[Fisk] Vanessa!

33
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:32,292
[doctor] Sir, sir. Mr. Mayor,
I understand that you are anxious,

34
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:35,208
and we will get you all the information
as soon as possible.

35
00:03:35,292 --> 00:03:37,500
-Can you...
-Yes, yes. Okay. Sir.

36
00:03:37,583 --> 00:03:39,125
-Sir, please.
-Sir, please.

37
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:41,708
-Sir, please.
-Sir, let them do their job.

38
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:55,500
[Sheila] All hands on deck.

39
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:57,167
I need you to clear the schedule.

40
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,792
-Yes! You need to...
-Like I said, absolutely no comment.

41
00:04:00,875 --> 00:04:02,792
How many times
do I have to tell you this, huh?

42
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:03,958
I'm not gonna have to... I don't know when

43
00:04:04,042 --> 00:04:05,833
-a statement's gonna be ready, all right?
-[Sheila] Yes. Yes, go.

44
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,042
If you have them...

45
00:04:12,625 --> 00:04:13,750
keep them alive.

46
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:15,458
Uh, we don't, sir.

47
00:04:15,917 --> 00:04:16,917
Not yet.

48
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:19,667
Pretty sure we have them surrounded.

49
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:22,792
Sir, I want to find them as bad as you do.

50
00:04:23,042 --> 00:04:24,042
No.

51
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:26,708
You don't.

52
00:04:27,583 --> 00:04:28,667
You couldn't.

53
00:04:30,125 --> 00:04:32,167
Whatever you need, use it.

54
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:33,667
You got it, sir.

55
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,667
Officer Powell...

56
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:39,250
Alive.

57
00:04:41,917 --> 00:04:42,917
Yeah.

58
00:04:48,458 --> 00:04:49,833
[officer 1] The tower is ready.
Have a seat.

59
00:04:49,917 --> 00:04:51,542
[officer 2] Let's move out.
Check that side.

60
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:01,125
-Go, go, go, go, go!
-Over here.

61
00:05:01,208 --> 00:05:02,333
-Here, here.
-Let's go.

62
00:05:04,792 --> 00:05:08,125
-[panting, groaning]
-[staff chattering indistinctly]

63
00:05:10,083 --> 00:05:11,583
[Daredevil] Prep towels, where are they?

64
00:05:13,917 --> 00:05:16,167
-Now!
-Whatever you need, man. We're with you.

65
00:05:17,542 --> 00:05:19,292
You don't have to do this.

66
00:05:19,375 --> 00:05:20,417
-Hold still.
-This is balance.

67
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,083
-You know it.
-Shut up.

68
00:05:22,167 --> 00:05:26,042
-[sirens echoing]
-[officer] Check in there. Check the door!

69
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:28,417
-Do you have a boiler?
-Yeah, old shit back there.

70
00:05:29,458 --> 00:05:31,458
-Yeah, let's go.
-Leave me here.

71
00:05:31,958 --> 00:05:33,208
None of this matters now.

72
00:05:33,292 --> 00:05:34,667
-It matters to me.
-[grunts]

73
00:05:36,542 --> 00:05:37,792
Yeah, uh...

74
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:39,292
No, no comment on that.

75
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:42,875
I don't know when we're gonna have
a statement ready. No.

76
00:05:44,958 --> 00:05:45,958
Is she dead?

77
00:05:47,042 --> 00:05:49,833
What kind of sick
fucking question is that?

78
00:05:49,917 --> 00:05:52,417
-[sighs]
-[call ends]

79
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,583
[phone chimes]

80
00:06:02,750 --> 00:06:05,750
[man on PA speaking indistinctly]

81
00:06:06,125 --> 00:06:07,458
How did you find me here?

82
00:06:07,542 --> 00:06:10,083
Seriously? I mean, how many hospitals
do you think there are, Daniel?

83
00:06:10,167 --> 00:06:12,125
-BB, you can't be here right now.
-Um...

84
00:06:12,208 --> 00:06:15,208
-Actually, technically, legally, I can.
-BB, think.

85
00:06:15,292 --> 00:06:17,083
Nobody can know where she is.
It's... It's...

86
00:06:17,958 --> 00:06:20,417
The mayor's not in a good place.
You gotta go.

87
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,500
Okay.

88
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,833
I-- I get it. I'll go, but just tell me.

89
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,000
Is she alive?

90
00:06:27,542 --> 00:06:30,208
Look, there's a ton of chatter out there.
You have no idea.

91
00:06:30,292 --> 00:06:31,625
It's, like, crazy right now.

92
00:06:31,708 --> 00:06:34,000
And I just want to make sure
I get the story right.

93
00:06:36,708 --> 00:06:38,833
We're really fucking
doing this right now, huh?

94
00:06:44,708 --> 00:06:46,542
I... I'm so sorry.

95
00:06:48,125 --> 00:06:51,000
I shouldn't have come.
Just forget that I came, okay?

96
00:07:01,292 --> 00:07:03,042
She's in critical condition.

97
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,833
They're... They're really lucky
to have you.

98
00:07:19,792 --> 00:07:20,792
[man] Mr. Fisk.

99
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:24,375
Mr. Fisk.

100
00:07:27,917 --> 00:07:29,000
Arash Merati.

101
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,000
Happy to meet you.

102
00:07:31,083 --> 00:07:32,167
Dr. Merati.

103
00:07:33,167 --> 00:07:35,500
Please understand that
I am here to do whatever I can

104
00:07:35,583 --> 00:07:37,042
-for your beloved wife.
-Yeah.

105
00:07:37,542 --> 00:07:39,500
I had a chance to look over her chart.

106
00:07:40,292 --> 00:07:43,042
She is, as you know,
in quite a precarious position.

107
00:07:43,125 --> 00:07:44,125
Yes.

108
00:07:44,625 --> 00:07:46,000
I've heard that you're...

109
00:07:46,792 --> 00:07:48,542
the top man in your field.

110
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:52,292
Well nothing is certain where the mind
meets the soul, Mr. Fisk.

111
00:07:53,042 --> 00:07:56,083
But that said, I will do
everything in my power for her.

112
00:07:56,167 --> 00:07:57,208
Thank you.

113
00:08:06,458 --> 00:08:09,167
[woman] Knowing what a disaster
Verizon is in Chelsea,

114
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:13,958
I can only imagine what sort of
cellular joy awaits me in central Vermont.

115
00:08:14,917 --> 00:08:18,125
-Hello.
-[woman speaking indistinctly]

116
00:08:33,417 --> 00:08:37,583
May I ask why you chose
not to include this piece tonight?

117
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:40,333
I think it's pretty obvious
why I chose not to include it,

118
00:08:40,417 --> 00:08:43,958
but if you feel differently,
by all means, why should I put it up?

119
00:08:46,292 --> 00:08:47,292
[Vanessa] I don't know.

120
00:08:47,542 --> 00:08:49,375
There's just something about it.

121
00:08:52,583 --> 00:08:54,083
Do you understand

122
00:08:54,167 --> 00:08:55,875
what keeps us in business?

123
00:08:55,958 --> 00:08:59,708
What pays for the cute little
gray shoes that you're wearing?

124
00:09:02,292 --> 00:09:03,667
But I can tell you...

125
00:09:06,458 --> 00:09:10,333
that if the right person
walks through that door

126
00:09:11,292 --> 00:09:12,958
and sees this painting...

127
00:09:14,417 --> 00:09:16,708
sees his own deep, inexorable,

128
00:09:16,792 --> 00:09:20,667
miserable emptiness
reflected right back at him...

129
00:09:21,917 --> 00:09:23,375
I can promise you,

130
00:09:23,458 --> 00:09:25,917
you can add two zeros to the list price,

131
00:09:26,667 --> 00:09:30,833
and it'll sell faster
than any other piece out front.

132
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,208
The piece stays right where it is.

133
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:37,333
-[footsteps retreating]
-Your call.

134
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:49,958
[Dex] I'm bleeding out.

135
00:09:50,042 --> 00:09:51,667
I've seen it enough times to know.

136
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:53,500
[Daredevil] I'm not interested
in your opinion.

137
00:09:54,708 --> 00:09:55,958
I've earned this...

138
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,375
many times over. It's okay.

139
00:10:02,167 --> 00:10:03,250
[grunts]

140
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,708
[breathing raggedly]

141
00:10:06,917 --> 00:10:08,167
You think she's dead?

142
00:10:10,208 --> 00:10:11,208
I don't know.

143
00:10:12,792 --> 00:10:13,792
Come on.

144
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:17,167
And if she is, it all balances.

145
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:20,667
Your friend, Fisk's wife.

146
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:24,292
Scales settled.

147
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,833
-And I'm ready for judgment.
-Oh, good for you.

148
00:10:28,917 --> 00:10:30,167
You're not listening.

149
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:35,500
That night you threw me off the roof,
I was supposed to die.

150
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,250
Four-story. No one survives that.

151
00:10:38,917 --> 00:10:39,917
And yet...

152
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:42,417
Maybe that's the grand design.

153
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:45,208
You're getting it.

154
00:10:46,417 --> 00:10:47,625
No, I'm not getting it.

155
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,083
If she's dead. Vanessa.

156
00:10:52,208 --> 00:10:53,292
That's just murder.

157
00:10:53,375 --> 00:10:54,958
Vanessa, Foggy--

158
00:10:55,042 --> 00:10:56,750
[choking]

159
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:02,500
Don't say his name.

160
00:11:04,792 --> 00:11:07,083
You don't get to say his name.
Do you understand?

161
00:11:08,542 --> 00:11:12,208
-You-- [groans]
-Tell me you understand.

162
00:11:12,292 --> 00:11:13,417
Don't say his name.

163
00:11:16,708 --> 00:11:19,208
[Foggy] Even the best avocados
have to do grunt work.

164
00:11:19,292 --> 00:11:21,667
[Matt] I guess we're gonna have to
break it to Josie that we're not

165
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:24,208
-paying off the tab tonight.
-She'll understand.

166
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:28,292
Lionel McCoy, 29 years old,
possession of multiple narcotics,

167
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:30,167
including, but not limited to,

168
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:32,417
Oxy, Moxy, Roxy,

169
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:34,167
and wait for it, Xoxy.

170
00:11:34,250 --> 00:11:36,250
[chuckles] Christ,
guy's a walking pharmacy.

171
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:39,208
Throw in a firearms charge, fake ID,

172
00:11:39,292 --> 00:11:41,583
intent to distribute,
obstruction of justice.

173
00:11:42,583 --> 00:11:44,875
Some yada. A little more yada
and yet another yada.

174
00:11:44,958 --> 00:11:46,583
And this guy is looking down the barrel--

175
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:48,583
Wait, wait, wait. Okay, hold on.
Let me guess.

176
00:11:49,292 --> 00:11:51,500
I want to say 12 to 15.

177
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:53,458
I'm sorry, Mr. Murdock.

178
00:11:53,542 --> 00:11:55,875
-The answer is actually 10 to 12.
-Oh, come on.

179
00:11:55,958 --> 00:11:57,833
-I was so close.
-But thank you for playing with us.

180
00:11:57,917 --> 00:11:59,583
And we do hope you enjoyed your stay

181
00:11:59,667 --> 00:12:02,208
-in the correctional facility.
-[chuckles]

182
00:12:02,292 --> 00:12:04,250
Okay, what do you say?
Uh, we ask for six to eight,

183
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:05,875
he's out in five for good behavior.

184
00:12:05,958 --> 00:12:09,833
Yep. Levine wants him to plead out,
so we take the best offer on the table.

185
00:12:09,917 --> 00:12:12,750
Under no circumstances
does this go to trial.

186
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:13,833
Heard.

187
00:12:13,917 --> 00:12:14,958
After you, Counselor.

188
00:12:15,042 --> 00:12:16,583
Why, thank you, Counselor.

189
00:12:20,708 --> 00:12:23,750
Good afternoon, Mr. McCoy.
My name is Matthew Murdock.

190
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,833
-This is my associate--
-Foggy the Fembot?

191
00:12:28,083 --> 00:12:29,292
Ray?

192
00:12:29,375 --> 00:12:31,250
[chuckles] You-- You know each other?

193
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,625
Guy upstairs got a sick
sense of humor, don't he?

194
00:12:33,708 --> 00:12:35,167
We, um...

195
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:38,708
grew up in the same building.

196
00:12:39,708 --> 00:12:41,083
Isn't your name Ray?

197
00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:43,917
[Lionel] What, you think I'd go by Lionel
in that neighborhood?

198
00:12:44,458 --> 00:12:46,792
You know, Fembot,
he used to clean my sneakers.

199
00:12:47,833 --> 00:12:49,542
-Didn't you?
-Maybe we could refrain

200
00:12:49,625 --> 00:12:51,042
from the name-calling, Mr. McCoy?

201
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:53,125
-What's with him? You blind or something?
-[Foggy] How--

202
00:12:53,208 --> 00:12:55,167
How's, um, Connor?

203
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:57,083
He moved upstate last year.

204
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:58,958
Oneonta.

205
00:12:59,625 --> 00:13:01,875
I don't know.
Last I heard he was doing roofs.

206
00:13:01,958 --> 00:13:04,250
Some shit like that.
Gutters, maybe. I don't know.

207
00:13:04,667 --> 00:13:06,458
Knocked up the first chick he could.

208
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,292
Okay, maybe we should, uh...

209
00:13:09,375 --> 00:13:11,167
Oh, yeah, please.

210
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:15,583
We, uh, used to... hang out.

211
00:13:15,667 --> 00:13:17,500
Me and his brother, I mean.

212
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:18,792
We were best friends.

213
00:13:18,875 --> 00:13:21,292
-The aforementioned Connor.
-Mmm-hmm.

214
00:13:21,708 --> 00:13:24,167
All right, uh, Mr. McCoy,
you're facing a laundry list

215
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:25,667
-of state charges. I suggest--
-It's all bullshit.

216
00:13:25,750 --> 00:13:27,750
Regardless,
our firm was retained to represent you,

217
00:13:27,833 --> 00:13:30,125
-and Mr. Nelson and I would like--
-[Lionel snickers]

218
00:13:31,042 --> 00:13:32,042
You Mr. Nelson?

219
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:34,792
-Is that supposed to be you?
-Foggy?

220
00:13:35,625 --> 00:13:38,208
You wanna tell your friend here what
the firm's professional advice would be?

221
00:13:38,292 --> 00:13:40,292
-Yeah, yeah. Go ahead, Mr. Nelson.
-[clears throat]

222
00:13:41,042 --> 00:13:42,042
What do you got?

223
00:13:43,208 --> 00:13:45,833
Right. Well, we, um...

224
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,667
Given the charges,
the evidence against you,

225
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:52,542
we suggest that you take a plea deal.

226
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:56,333
We ask for a reduction in sentencing.

227
00:13:56,417 --> 00:13:58,458
And best case scenario, you're out in...

228
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:02,000
-five to six.
-Or three to four with exemplary behavior.

229
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:04,000
-[Lionel] Oh, five to six.
-Three to four if you...

230
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:05,708
If, if, if, if, if I what?

231
00:14:05,792 --> 00:14:07,417
If I-- If I find God?

232
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:10,708
Huh? If I-- If I mop the john?
Wait the library?

233
00:14:10,792 --> 00:14:12,833
I believe they call it rehabilitation,
Mr. McCoy.

234
00:14:12,917 --> 00:14:14,167
Mmm-hmm. You don't understand.

235
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:17,000
The guys I work with want me dead.

236
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,833
I mean, that's the whole reason
you two are even here in the first place.

237
00:14:20,917 --> 00:14:21,958
Cop a deal,

238
00:14:22,042 --> 00:14:23,333
they told you, right?

239
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:26,792
No trial. Huh?

240
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:28,625
You want to know why?

241
00:14:29,375 --> 00:14:33,708
Because they got about ten guys
on the inside just waiting to take me out.

242
00:14:33,792 --> 00:14:35,250
All right? That's how this ends.

243
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:37,833
That's how this goes.
All right? So, it's not three to four,

244
00:14:37,917 --> 00:14:40,208
it's not six to eight
if I'm a little good boy. All right?

245
00:14:40,292 --> 00:14:42,667
It's 24 hours, counselor.

246
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:45,667
I'm a dead man the second I go in.

247
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:47,417
So...

248
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,708
I'm not signing shit.

249
00:14:52,167 --> 00:14:54,125
I'll take my chances
with a public defender.

250
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:56,208
All right. Take it easy.
Back-- Back up here.

251
00:14:56,292 --> 00:14:58,542
What-- [sighs] What are you talking about?

252
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:02,458
You two don't even know
who you work for, do you?

253
00:15:09,792 --> 00:15:11,917
[cell phone buzzing]

254
00:15:13,708 --> 00:15:14,833
This is Wesley.

255
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:18,458
Right.

256
00:15:20,250 --> 00:15:21,250
I'll let you know.

257
00:15:25,542 --> 00:15:28,042
We may have an issue with the Lion.

258
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,792
Are you familiar with Bitcoin?

259
00:15:36,875 --> 00:15:38,292
In light of the Russians...

260
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:43,375
we should start diversifying.

261
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:47,458
In this new world...

262
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:53,958
we can no longer be old-fashioned
in our way of thinking.

263
00:15:55,250 --> 00:15:57,750
I do have some contacts
in the crypto space,

264
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,542
but if I may, I would suggest

265
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:02,667
it might be too volatile

266
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:04,292
for our needs, sir.

267
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:08,500
Hmm. Now, perhaps you have other ideas.

268
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:11,042
Come to think of it,

269
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:14,833
I have a friend who runs an art gallery.

270
00:16:16,417 --> 00:16:19,333
Blue chip. Real money.

271
00:16:20,542 --> 00:16:22,625
It could be an interesting market for us.

272
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:25,833
The art world.

273
00:16:26,792 --> 00:16:27,833
Pretension.

274
00:16:29,167 --> 00:16:33,000
And airs of posing as something...

275
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:35,833
meaningful.

276
00:16:37,875 --> 00:16:39,458
[medical machine beeping slowly]

277
00:17:02,250 --> 00:17:03,292
[Daredevil] Keep moving.

278
00:17:03,375 --> 00:17:04,583
We need to get you help.

279
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:07,625
-[groans]
-No, no, no. No!

280
00:17:07,708 --> 00:17:09,125
No, no! Come on.

281
00:17:09,208 --> 00:17:10,792
-[wheezing]
-Stop it.

282
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:13,792
-Stop! [grunts angrily]
-[Daredevil screams]

283
00:17:14,583 --> 00:17:17,625
[sighs] This is pointless.

284
00:17:17,708 --> 00:17:19,042
Let's be real.

285
00:17:19,667 --> 00:17:21,208
You're not gonna mourn me.

286
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:23,333
Go on, get up.

287
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:26,792
-You need help. Let's go.
-Mmm-mmm.

288
00:17:26,875 --> 00:17:29,250
-[Daredevil] Come on.
-Get your fucking hands off me!

289
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:32,000
-[Daredevil] Come on!
-[groaning]

290
00:17:35,542 --> 00:17:37,375
[Dex] First, you try to kill me,

291
00:17:37,917 --> 00:17:39,792
and then you try to save me,

292
00:17:41,042 --> 00:17:44,542
and I'm the one who needs help? [chuckles]

293
00:17:47,458 --> 00:17:50,083
I'm trying to save you
because I tried to kill you.

294
00:17:51,750 --> 00:17:53,542
I lost sight of that on Josie's roof.

295
00:17:55,625 --> 00:17:57,583
Maybe tonight's penance is mutual.

296
00:18:00,125 --> 00:18:01,125
Come on.

297
00:18:01,833 --> 00:18:04,500
-Come on.
-[grunting]

298
00:18:09,083 --> 00:18:11,125
[grunting]

299
00:18:11,875 --> 00:18:12,917
You said Henderson?

300
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,667
-Hernandez.
-[Matt] Oh, damn.

301
00:18:16,792 --> 00:18:19,250
All right. Punching out
before the elevator rush.

302
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:20,500
Have you got plans?

303
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:22,833
Allowance?

304
00:18:22,917 --> 00:18:24,000
[Matt] Oh, that's right.

305
00:18:24,958 --> 00:18:26,583
What are we, uh... What are we up to?

306
00:18:27,708 --> 00:18:30,875
Seventeen-hundred even as of tonight.

307
00:18:30,958 --> 00:18:34,042
[whistles] What do you think?
Eighteen more months

308
00:18:34,125 --> 00:18:36,333
before we open doors
on Murdock and Nelson?

309
00:18:36,417 --> 00:18:38,000
[Jeff] Congratulations, fuckos.

310
00:18:38,667 --> 00:18:40,292
Great job at the precinct today.

311
00:18:40,375 --> 00:18:42,208
All you had to do
was have the guy sign his name.

312
00:18:42,292 --> 00:18:43,708
Didn't even have to be legible.

313
00:18:43,792 --> 00:18:45,875
Plead out, sign the papers, move on.

314
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:48,042
-But, no.
-Jeff, we...

315
00:18:48,125 --> 00:18:50,417
I'm sorry. Did you mean "Mr. Levine"?

316
00:18:51,208 --> 00:18:53,250
Right, yes. Sorry.

317
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:54,917
-Mr. Levine, we--
-Guess what?

318
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:56,333
I don't care.

319
00:18:56,958 --> 00:18:58,833
It's the public defender's problem now,
isn't it?

320
00:18:59,625 --> 00:19:01,792
Unfortunately, they need all these papers,

321
00:19:01,875 --> 00:19:04,458
collated and delivered to their office
by Monday morning.

322
00:19:05,458 --> 00:19:07,000
Happy Fraturday, fucknuts.

323
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:10,333
Have a nice weekend.

324
00:19:10,417 --> 00:19:11,500
[chuckles]

325
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:14,958
[Matt] He's definitely into
something weird.

326
00:19:15,042 --> 00:19:16,875
Totally. Like feet.

327
00:19:17,708 --> 00:19:19,042
[chuckles] What's wrong with feet?

328
00:19:19,417 --> 00:19:21,042
Nothing. I'm just saying that

329
00:19:21,125 --> 00:19:22,417
I can imagine Mr. Levine

330
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:24,750
doing some weird shit with feet.
That's all.

331
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:25,833
[Matt] Gross.

332
00:19:28,042 --> 00:19:29,625
Exhibit C, column two.

333
00:19:29,708 --> 00:19:31,292
Column two, exhibit C.

334
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,333
Just, uh, for the record,

335
00:19:34,792 --> 00:19:36,708
I don't have a problem with feet.

336
00:19:36,792 --> 00:19:38,667
You're also not not weird, so...

337
00:19:38,750 --> 00:19:39,750
[chuckles]

338
00:19:41,583 --> 00:19:42,583
Whoa.

339
00:19:43,917 --> 00:19:44,917
What?

340
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,250
The warrant.

341
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:50,000
The address on the warrant they used
to access his apartment, it's wrong.

342
00:19:50,542 --> 00:19:53,958
It says 536 West 49th Street,
apartment 5E.

343
00:19:54,583 --> 00:19:55,625
That isn't correct?

344
00:19:55,708 --> 00:19:57,333
It's 536 1/2.

345
00:19:57,708 --> 00:20:00,208
That's where he lived.
The McCoys, I mean, that was our address.

346
00:20:00,292 --> 00:20:02,458
536 1/2 West 49th.

347
00:20:04,083 --> 00:20:05,500
No, that-- That can't be right.

348
00:20:05,583 --> 00:20:06,833
It is right.

349
00:20:07,917 --> 00:20:09,958
I mean, it's a clerical error, but...

350
00:20:11,625 --> 00:20:12,750
this is invalid.

351
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:17,292
Everything discovered in this warrant
is fruit of the poison tree.

352
00:20:17,375 --> 00:20:18,375
It's inadmissible.

353
00:20:19,917 --> 00:20:22,042
Which means that piece of paper is...

354
00:20:22,667 --> 00:20:24,333
Get-out-of-jail free card.

355
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:29,750
What do we do?

356
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:35,833
Oh, come on, Foggy.
It's not like he deserves to walk.

357
00:20:35,917 --> 00:20:38,000
I don't recall the word "deserve"

358
00:20:38,083 --> 00:20:39,375
coming up in law school.

359
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:41,708
He's in bed with the mob,
he's selling drugs,

360
00:20:41,792 --> 00:20:43,333
he's poisoning the neighborhood.

361
00:20:43,417 --> 00:20:44,750
[Foggy] Yeah, but...

362
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:48,292
But what? He was also a raging prick
to you when you were kids?

363
00:20:48,375 --> 00:20:51,125
You want to spring the guy
who calls you Foggy the Fembot?

364
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,292
[scoffs] No, I don't.

365
00:20:54,292 --> 00:20:55,292
But, Matt...

366
00:20:55,750 --> 00:20:57,042
we are his attorneys.

367
00:20:57,125 --> 00:20:59,542
-We're associates.
-Don't get technical.

368
00:20:59,625 --> 00:21:01,792
-Either way, Jeff made it sound like--
-Mr. Levine.

369
00:21:01,875 --> 00:21:03,417
-Thank you.
-[chuckles] Okay, okay, fine.

370
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:06,208
Dark Lord of Unspoken Kink Levine

371
00:21:06,292 --> 00:21:08,417
made it sound like
we're not only off the case,

372
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:10,458
but our badges might not work on Monday.

373
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:12,667
Ray, Lionel...

374
00:21:13,125 --> 00:21:14,625
he had a hard life, Matt.

375
00:21:14,708 --> 00:21:16,458
[sarcastically] Aw! Cue the violin.

376
00:21:16,542 --> 00:21:19,167
His dad, he was not a good guy.

377
00:21:19,250 --> 00:21:20,958
And their mom, Suzanne, she drank.

378
00:21:21,042 --> 00:21:23,625
A lot. She died when we were
in the eighth grade.

379
00:21:23,708 --> 00:21:24,708
Okay?

380
00:21:24,792 --> 00:21:27,000
Cirrhosis, liver failure.

381
00:21:27,208 --> 00:21:29,292
-[Matt sighs]
-He never had a chance.

382
00:21:29,375 --> 00:21:31,333
His brother did though, didn't he?
What was his name? Connor?

383
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,333
Connor was younger.

384
00:21:33,583 --> 00:21:35,125
Lionel took the brunt of it.

385
00:21:35,208 --> 00:21:37,833
-I didn't like him.
-And you want to let him out

386
00:21:37,917 --> 00:21:40,917
to continue to do horrendous things
to a whole bunch of new people.

387
00:21:41,667 --> 00:21:44,000
-I want to do the right thing.
-I don't know, Foggy.

388
00:21:44,083 --> 00:21:45,083
I don't know.

389
00:21:46,458 --> 00:21:49,042
You sell drugs, you're trafficking
firearms, you get caught.

390
00:21:49,125 --> 00:21:50,708
I'm sorry. There are consequences.

391
00:21:50,792 --> 00:21:53,583
His crew, whoever he was working with,

392
00:21:53,667 --> 00:21:55,833
they're gonna kill him when he's inside.

393
00:21:55,917 --> 00:21:58,125
Yeah, that might be
the definition of consequences.

394
00:21:58,208 --> 00:22:00,167
But does the punishment fit the crime?

395
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:02,500
-Crimes past, present or future?
-So you think we should ignore it?

396
00:22:02,583 --> 00:22:04,500
-Ignore what?
-It's our job

397
00:22:04,583 --> 00:22:05,875
to represent our clients

398
00:22:05,958 --> 00:22:08,542
to the best of our abilities.
Suppressing evidence--

399
00:22:08,625 --> 00:22:10,625
Objection. "Suppressing" is questionable.

400
00:22:10,708 --> 00:22:13,583
One might even say inflammatory phrasing
in this particular instance, Counselor.

401
00:22:13,667 --> 00:22:15,583
Aren't you supposed to be
the Catholic one here?

402
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:18,708
Oh, come on. All right, so, fine,
you want to go with guilt now?

403
00:22:23,042 --> 00:22:24,458
How about mercy?

404
00:22:25,708 --> 00:22:28,208
There's got to be something
about that in the Bible.

405
00:22:29,167 --> 00:22:30,500
Second chances,

406
00:22:31,042 --> 00:22:32,083
redemption?

407
00:22:33,750 --> 00:22:36,792
All I know is if he goes to jail, he dies.

408
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:41,375
And all I know is that
might not be our problem.

409
00:22:41,958 --> 00:22:43,500
Unfortunately...

410
00:22:44,542 --> 00:22:45,583
it is now.

411
00:22:48,625 --> 00:22:49,708
[cell phone buzzes]

412
00:22:49,792 --> 00:22:50,792
This is Wesley.

413
00:22:51,125 --> 00:22:52,583
That's great to hear.

414
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:54,625
Let me talk to him. I'll call you back.

415
00:22:56,042 --> 00:22:57,625
I take it he's available?

416
00:22:58,417 --> 00:23:00,333
He's here for a couple of weeks, just...

417
00:23:01,083 --> 00:23:02,208
moving through town.

418
00:23:02,292 --> 00:23:04,083
He's good. Very good.

419
00:23:04,958 --> 00:23:06,000
Maybe the best.

420
00:23:07,667 --> 00:23:08,667
Use him.

421
00:23:09,875 --> 00:23:11,625
-[cell phone beeps]
-We're a go.

422
00:23:15,458 --> 00:23:17,625
[anchor] His approval ratings
suggest otherwise.

423
00:23:17,708 --> 00:23:18,958
[reporter] Good afternoon, Brian.

424
00:23:19,042 --> 00:23:21,292
Breaking news, just in to New York One.

425
00:23:21,375 --> 00:23:24,583
I am standing just outside
the entrance to Metro General Hospital.

426
00:23:24,667 --> 00:23:27,000
here on Fifth Avenue, where we understand

427
00:23:27,083 --> 00:23:29,417
Vanessa Fisk is in critical condition.

428
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:31,250
Fucking BB, no way.

429
00:23:31,333 --> 00:23:33,333
[reporter] ...in last night's
violent attack on...

430
00:23:33,417 --> 00:23:34,417
-Mr. Blake.
-No way.

431
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:35,875
-Can I get an update on Mrs. Fisk?
-No way. No.

432
00:23:35,958 --> 00:23:38,417
-Can you do me a favor and fuck off?
-And who the hell are you?

433
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,500
I'm the one telling you
to fuck off. Keep up.

434
00:23:40,875 --> 00:23:42,375
Do I need to call the Task Force?

435
00:23:46,667 --> 00:23:48,000
They're horrible. Trust me.

436
00:23:53,250 --> 00:23:54,292
Thanks for that.

437
00:23:56,583 --> 00:23:57,583
[sighs]

438
00:23:58,958 --> 00:23:59,958
Tough day.

439
00:24:00,042 --> 00:24:01,042
The worst.

440
00:24:02,167 --> 00:24:03,792
Buck, where were you last night?

441
00:24:04,583 --> 00:24:05,750
I had to run an errand.

442
00:24:06,667 --> 00:24:08,125
-How is he?
-Better.

443
00:24:08,875 --> 00:24:10,125
She's out of surgery.

444
00:24:10,208 --> 00:24:12,583
It's too soon to tell,
but it's not bad news so far.

445
00:24:12,667 --> 00:24:14,000
-Thank Christ.
-Mmm-hmm.

446
00:24:15,750 --> 00:24:17,458
You know, I could kill for a hot dog.

447
00:24:19,208 --> 00:24:20,417
Yeah, sure.

448
00:24:20,875 --> 00:24:21,875
Come on.

449
00:24:24,667 --> 00:24:25,667
[Fisk] It's done.

450
00:24:26,208 --> 00:24:27,250
[Dr. Merati] Yes.

451
00:24:27,333 --> 00:24:28,333
Yes, indeed.

452
00:24:29,167 --> 00:24:30,458
The surgery went quite well.

453
00:24:31,833 --> 00:24:32,958
Tell me everything.

454
00:24:33,750 --> 00:24:36,917
[Dr. Merati] Well, the procedure was long,
as you know, and quite involved.

455
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,000
But...

456
00:24:38,417 --> 00:24:40,333
I'm optimistic in nature.

457
00:24:40,833 --> 00:24:41,958
And I remain hopeful.

458
00:24:43,375 --> 00:24:44,375
Hope?

459
00:24:47,708 --> 00:24:49,333
She's gonna be fine.

460
00:24:53,833 --> 00:24:55,500
[Vanessa] Please lean it against the wall.

461
00:24:55,583 --> 00:24:57,250
I'll deal with it later.

462
00:24:58,500 --> 00:24:59,708
[exhales]

463
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:04,167
So, same spot, different piece?

464
00:25:04,250 --> 00:25:05,292
Mmm-hmm.

465
00:25:06,708 --> 00:25:08,542
I hope you know what you're doing.

466
00:25:21,792 --> 00:25:23,167
[waves lapping shore]

467
00:25:26,250 --> 00:25:27,583
[♪ melancholy music playing]

468
00:25:57,125 --> 00:26:00,292
You know, there's hot dog carts
on every corner.

469
00:26:00,375 --> 00:26:02,167
[Buck] Yeah,
I thought we might take a drive.

470
00:26:02,250 --> 00:26:03,333
Have a little chat.

471
00:26:03,417 --> 00:26:04,542
A chat?

472
00:26:04,625 --> 00:26:06,458
Buck, Fisk needs me.

473
00:26:06,542 --> 00:26:08,875
The man is aware we're going to Albany.

474
00:26:08,958 --> 00:26:10,958
Yo, Albany?

475
00:26:12,417 --> 00:26:14,375
Dude, you didn't say
anything about Albany.

476
00:26:16,667 --> 00:26:19,667
The other day in your office,
you were asking about my background.

477
00:26:20,042 --> 00:26:22,042
-Yeah, sure.
-Well, you were right.

478
00:26:22,667 --> 00:26:23,833
I was Regiment 22.

479
00:26:26,958 --> 00:26:30,458
When you were reading about my past,
did you see anything about Helmand?

480
00:26:31,792 --> 00:26:32,792
The mayonnaise?

481
00:26:34,333 --> 00:26:36,042
No, Daniel, not the mayonnaise.

482
00:26:36,625 --> 00:26:37,667
Afghanistan.

483
00:26:39,167 --> 00:26:43,125
My squadron, and I imagine many others,
were tasked with night raids,

484
00:26:43,208 --> 00:26:46,542
that no man of fighting age
would survive the night.

485
00:26:47,375 --> 00:26:49,958
But it was opium farmers, not insurgents.

486
00:26:50,042 --> 00:26:52,750
Apparently, Her Majesty
considered 14 fighting age.

487
00:26:55,583 --> 00:26:57,208
Jesus Christ, what did you do?

488
00:27:00,042 --> 00:27:01,167
What I was ordered to.

489
00:27:02,958 --> 00:27:03,958
That's my point.

490
00:27:05,833 --> 00:27:08,083
There are pivotal moments
in a man's life, Daniel,

491
00:27:08,167 --> 00:27:11,292
which define what kind of man he is,

492
00:27:11,792 --> 00:27:12,958
what he's really made of.

493
00:27:13,458 --> 00:27:16,000
Mr. Fisk changed my life
in one of those moments.

494
00:27:16,625 --> 00:27:18,083
I imagine you can relate, right?

495
00:27:19,292 --> 00:27:21,167
Staten Island to City Hall.

496
00:27:21,625 --> 00:27:23,083
Head of communications.

497
00:27:23,833 --> 00:27:25,417
That's quite a trajectory.

498
00:27:27,333 --> 00:27:28,792
That's impressive, Daniel.

499
00:27:30,625 --> 00:27:31,708
Appreciate that.

500
00:27:31,792 --> 00:27:33,792
My God, it has not been easy, has it?

501
00:27:34,417 --> 00:27:36,875
Muse, The Northern Star leak.

502
00:27:38,042 --> 00:27:41,750
And now it seems someone, God knows who,
has leaked the hospital to the press.

503
00:27:45,208 --> 00:27:47,292
What? You're not saying you think it's me,
are you?

504
00:27:48,750 --> 00:27:50,958
Buck, I didn't have
anything to do with that.

505
00:27:52,042 --> 00:27:53,500
Let's just take a left in here.

506
00:28:06,958 --> 00:28:08,333
Buck, am I in trouble?

507
00:28:11,042 --> 00:28:12,167
Be right back.

508
00:28:13,250 --> 00:28:14,708
Well, maybe I'll just come in with you.

509
00:28:14,792 --> 00:28:17,167
Get some beef jerky or help you out,
or whatever.

510
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,375
That's kind of you, Daniel.
But I'll take care of it.

511
00:28:21,542 --> 00:28:22,625
Just sit tight, yeah?

512
00:28:39,208 --> 00:28:41,458
[breathing nervously]

513
00:28:42,708 --> 00:28:46,667
-[car beeping]
-[exhales]

514
00:28:50,583 --> 00:28:53,333
[thudding]

515
00:28:56,583 --> 00:28:57,750
[nervously] Mmm!

516
00:29:37,750 --> 00:29:38,917
[car door closes]

517
00:29:46,583 --> 00:29:47,917
[Wesley] Long time, pal.

518
00:29:48,917 --> 00:29:50,542
[chuckles] Looking good, Wes.

519
00:29:51,292 --> 00:29:53,750
Fucking hell.
You've come up in the world, haven't you?

520
00:29:54,083 --> 00:29:55,292
Living the dream.

521
00:29:56,208 --> 00:29:58,500
I understand you have
some sort of open assignment.

522
00:29:59,292 --> 00:30:00,792
We're looking to you for...

523
00:30:01,333 --> 00:30:02,500
creativity.

524
00:30:08,083 --> 00:30:10,333
[Buck] Well, you've come to
the right place, then, haven't you?

525
00:30:12,167 --> 00:30:14,667
-[door buzzes]
-[officer] Sign here.

526
00:30:20,583 --> 00:30:21,750
Do you need anything?

527
00:30:24,458 --> 00:30:25,708
What are you gonna do now?

528
00:30:27,625 --> 00:30:28,958
What am I gonna do?

529
00:30:29,833 --> 00:30:32,375
I don't know.
Wait for 'em to come find me.

530
00:30:36,375 --> 00:30:38,250
All right. Good to see you, Fembot.

531
00:30:40,583 --> 00:30:42,417
[door opens]

532
00:30:43,792 --> 00:30:44,833
[groans]

533
00:30:44,917 --> 00:30:47,000
[Daredevil] You recognize this place,
you piece of shit?

534
00:30:47,083 --> 00:30:48,583
[sighs] Fuck.

535
00:30:48,667 --> 00:30:51,167
[panting]

536
00:30:55,667 --> 00:30:58,042
We should be safe here for now.

537
00:30:58,250 --> 00:31:01,125
[chuckles] Safe?

538
00:31:01,958 --> 00:31:03,458
What does that even mean?

539
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,958
You know what happens if she dies?

540
00:31:07,458 --> 00:31:09,917
Fisk turns the city upside-down
and shakes it

541
00:31:10,750 --> 00:31:12,083
until he finds us...

542
00:31:12,792 --> 00:31:13,917
and kills us.

543
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,250
Uh, me.

544
00:31:15,333 --> 00:31:16,667
-Kills me.
-Us.

545
00:31:16,750 --> 00:31:17,750
I was there.

546
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:20,375
That is more than enough for Fisk.

547
00:31:21,083 --> 00:31:22,083
[knocking on door]

548
00:31:31,500 --> 00:31:32,542
It's open.

549
00:31:37,375 --> 00:31:39,167
What the fuck you doing here, Foggy?

550
00:31:40,875 --> 00:31:42,750
[Daredevil] I know someone who can help.

551
00:31:43,333 --> 00:31:44,917
-A nurse.
-Nurses,

552
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,583
doctors...

553
00:31:47,417 --> 00:31:48,583
lawyers.

554
00:31:49,375 --> 00:31:51,875
Vigilantes, assassins.

555
00:31:52,792 --> 00:31:55,042
Killing people, saving people.

556
00:31:57,667 --> 00:31:59,375
Act like it makes a difference.

557
00:32:01,083 --> 00:32:02,708
Like it matters at all.

558
00:32:04,458 --> 00:32:05,792
[Foggy] I wanted to give you this.

559
00:32:09,042 --> 00:32:10,042
The hell is this?

560
00:32:10,625 --> 00:32:13,667
I was hoping you'd take that,
and, I don't know...

561
00:32:15,125 --> 00:32:16,125
get out of here.

562
00:32:16,208 --> 00:32:17,875
I don't even know where, but...

563
00:32:18,417 --> 00:32:19,875
Wait, wait, wait. So you--

564
00:32:19,958 --> 00:32:21,667
-You gonna give me money?
-No.

565
00:32:22,542 --> 00:32:24,708
Ray, I already gave it to you.

566
00:32:25,375 --> 00:32:28,375
What I want is for you
to start over with it.

567
00:32:28,875 --> 00:32:30,583
You got a second chance here.

568
00:32:31,042 --> 00:32:33,333
It's not about them. It's about you.

569
00:32:35,250 --> 00:32:36,250
About me.

570
00:32:38,375 --> 00:32:39,500
Just people...

571
00:32:42,333 --> 00:32:43,333
and, brother...

572
00:32:44,875 --> 00:32:47,292
we are who we are.

573
00:32:47,375 --> 00:32:49,750
[chuckles, coughs]

574
00:32:50,917 --> 00:32:52,208
[Lionel] You know those nights...

575
00:32:53,042 --> 00:32:54,042
we used to, uh...

576
00:32:55,417 --> 00:32:57,750
crash in the living room. Um...

577
00:32:59,417 --> 00:33:00,667
Well, you and Connor

578
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:03,625
with the, uh, sleeping bags and...
[chuckles]

579
00:33:03,708 --> 00:33:06,208
...uh, the flashlights, you know?

580
00:33:08,792 --> 00:33:11,250
I never really, uh,
had a friend like that.

581
00:33:12,917 --> 00:33:13,917
I know.

582
00:33:17,292 --> 00:33:18,958
[Dex] We're all doing the same thing here.

583
00:33:20,750 --> 00:33:23,625
Acting something out,
scratching some kinda itch.

584
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,292
But the worst part...

585
00:33:28,042 --> 00:33:29,833
is when you think you got it beat.

586
00:33:30,958 --> 00:33:32,042
You think...

587
00:33:33,208 --> 00:33:34,542
"I outran it."

588
00:33:37,500 --> 00:33:39,458
Then you turn the corner, bam...

589
00:33:41,750 --> 00:33:42,833
there it is...

590
00:33:44,583 --> 00:33:46,292
staring you right in the face.

591
00:33:48,792 --> 00:33:50,375
Only it's worse this time.

592
00:33:53,375 --> 00:33:54,417
And, you know...

593
00:33:57,667 --> 00:33:59,458
it was always gonna be there.

594
00:34:00,333 --> 00:34:01,792
[Lionel] Hey, do me a favor, will you?

595
00:34:02,417 --> 00:34:04,375
Tell my brother to stay
right where he's at.

596
00:34:05,833 --> 00:34:08,542
All right? You tell him
I told you to tell him that,

597
00:34:09,083 --> 00:34:11,125
that he ain't got nothing
back here for him.

598
00:34:14,083 --> 00:34:15,167
He's got you.

599
00:34:22,250 --> 00:34:24,250
Come on, Foggy. You gotta go, man.
Get out of here.

600
00:34:28,667 --> 00:34:30,167
[Dex] There's no escaping it.

601
00:34:36,875 --> 00:34:38,417
I'm sorry to interrupt.

602
00:34:38,792 --> 00:34:41,167
This church will always provide shelter

603
00:34:41,833 --> 00:34:43,125
to both of you, but...

604
00:34:44,625 --> 00:34:46,417
I think they know you're here.

605
00:34:47,042 --> 00:34:48,083
[banging on door]

606
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,375
Good evening, officers.
How can I help you?

607
00:34:54,458 --> 00:34:55,667
Hello, Father.

608
00:34:55,750 --> 00:34:58,583
You haven't by chance seen a couple of
vigilantes this fine evening, have you?

609
00:34:58,667 --> 00:35:02,000
I've been in prayers all afternoon,
Officer. I... I don't believe I have.

610
00:35:03,833 --> 00:35:05,583
[Dex groaning]

611
00:35:10,917 --> 00:35:13,208
Listen, we gotta come check the place out.
Mayor's orders.

612
00:35:15,458 --> 00:35:16,458
[Dex] Just...

613
00:35:17,500 --> 00:35:18,583
go.

614
00:35:19,750 --> 00:35:21,042
Don't be an idiot.

615
00:35:21,708 --> 00:35:22,833
Leave me.

616
00:35:23,250 --> 00:35:26,167
Oh, I'm sorry, but weapons are not
permitted in the house of God.

617
00:35:26,250 --> 00:35:27,625
The rules have changed.

618
00:35:28,500 --> 00:35:30,250
Come on in, boys. Sweep it!

619
00:35:31,583 --> 00:35:32,917
[Dex] I killed your friend...

620
00:35:33,292 --> 00:35:34,292
Foggy.

621
00:35:34,750 --> 00:35:36,125
I didn't think twice.

622
00:35:36,625 --> 00:35:38,167
That's who I am.

623
00:35:38,250 --> 00:35:39,875
[man yelling indistinctly]

624
00:35:43,708 --> 00:35:45,125
Just let me die.

625
00:35:47,292 --> 00:35:48,292
I don't...

626
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:52,417
[Daredevil] Look, I can't save us both.

627
00:35:52,500 --> 00:35:53,917
I'm sorry. I tried.

628
00:35:57,708 --> 00:35:59,292
[choking]

629
00:35:59,375 --> 00:36:01,125
[woman] Let's go! Let's go!

630
00:36:02,417 --> 00:36:05,000
-[siren blaring]
-[man] Sir! Let's go. Move!

631
00:36:07,333 --> 00:36:08,958
[Matt] Imagine my surprise...

632
00:36:10,167 --> 00:36:13,000
when I came back to the office
and found the empty book.

633
00:36:13,083 --> 00:36:14,167
How did you know?

634
00:36:14,250 --> 00:36:16,917
Spend enough time in the same tiny office
with the same person,

635
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,458
you tend to know what they're thinking.

636
00:36:25,125 --> 00:36:26,125
I'm sorry.

637
00:36:28,292 --> 00:36:29,458
I'll pay it back.

638
00:36:29,542 --> 00:36:30,542
[snickers]

639
00:36:33,083 --> 00:36:35,042
Foggy the Fembot. [chuckles]

640
00:36:35,958 --> 00:36:38,417
And there I was thinking
the Murdock and Nelson fund

641
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:40,333
was supposed to be about the future.

642
00:36:41,375 --> 00:36:42,875
It is, Matt.

643
00:36:44,792 --> 00:36:46,167
But not just ours.

644
00:36:50,958 --> 00:36:51,958
[Matt] So, where to now?

645
00:36:53,042 --> 00:36:54,750
-Josie's.
-Obviously.

646
00:36:54,833 --> 00:36:55,958
What are we celebrating?

647
00:36:58,417 --> 00:36:59,542
Mercy.

648
00:37:18,208 --> 00:37:19,208
Fuck.

649
00:37:21,792 --> 00:37:22,958
Where'd he go?

650
00:37:25,417 --> 00:37:26,458
[birds chirping softly]

651
00:37:41,917 --> 00:37:43,667
You really don't have to do this, man.

652
00:37:46,667 --> 00:37:48,667
I don't even know what I did.
But whatever it was,

653
00:37:48,750 --> 00:37:51,000
it was probably stupid,
and I probably deserve it.

654
00:37:52,083 --> 00:37:53,708
But I could just walk away, man.

655
00:37:54,500 --> 00:37:56,250
I could just disa-fucking-ppear,

656
00:37:56,333 --> 00:37:59,625
and you wouldn't hear anything from me.
Not a peep, not a tweet. Nothing.

657
00:38:01,583 --> 00:38:04,542
Man, I'd be like-- I'd be like Casper.
I mean, I'd be like a ghost.

658
00:38:10,958 --> 00:38:12,458
Look, I didn't fucking leak it.

659
00:38:13,250 --> 00:38:14,250
It wasn't me.

660
00:38:17,583 --> 00:38:18,583
I promise.

661
00:38:20,875 --> 00:38:22,333
Get out of the car, Daniel.

662
00:38:33,500 --> 00:38:34,500
Delivery.

663
00:38:52,583 --> 00:38:53,833
I like you, Daniel.

664
00:38:55,292 --> 00:38:56,417
I really do.

665
00:38:57,500 --> 00:38:59,625
But we work for a man
who can change your life.

666
00:39:01,375 --> 00:39:02,625
Has changed your life.

667
00:39:04,125 --> 00:39:05,625
And all he asks in return...

668
00:39:06,708 --> 00:39:07,708
is loyalty.

669
00:39:09,042 --> 00:39:10,125
Unbridled,

670
00:39:10,833 --> 00:39:12,125
unquestioned...

671
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:14,667
-loyalty.
-Well, I've been loyal.

672
00:39:15,375 --> 00:39:16,917
I've stayed loyal, Buck.

673
00:39:18,625 --> 00:39:19,833
I'll do anything.

674
00:39:21,083 --> 00:39:23,917
I've said it before.
I'll do whatever it takes.

675
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:25,083
Please.

676
00:39:26,958 --> 00:39:28,000
Make a choice.

677
00:39:35,292 --> 00:39:36,292
Saw...

678
00:39:36,958 --> 00:39:38,333
or shovel.

679
00:39:39,417 --> 00:39:41,083
[gasps softly]

680
00:39:59,708 --> 00:40:00,875
You know, I was thinking.

681
00:40:02,125 --> 00:40:03,750
Maybe, uh,

682
00:40:03,833 --> 00:40:05,708
instead of Murdock and Nelson,

683
00:40:06,167 --> 00:40:08,792
maybe it's Nelson and Murdock.

684
00:40:09,958 --> 00:40:11,292
-[Foggy] I like that.
-Yeah?

685
00:40:11,375 --> 00:40:12,375
I bumped you up.

686
00:40:12,458 --> 00:40:14,000
-[Foggy] I love that.
-You're goin' up in the world, buddy.

687
00:40:14,083 --> 00:40:15,750
-I am going up in the world.
-[Matt chuckles]

688
00:40:15,833 --> 00:40:18,458
And I think the next 50 rounds are on you.

689
00:40:18,542 --> 00:40:20,500
[Foggy] I don't know about 50.
Fifty sounds a little...

690
00:40:20,583 --> 00:40:22,708
-[Matt] Forty-nine. Sold.
-Forty-seven.

691
00:40:22,792 --> 00:40:24,583
[Daredevil grunting]

692
00:40:45,208 --> 00:40:46,625
Little help?

693
00:40:46,708 --> 00:40:48,125
[sighs in annoyance]

694
00:41:04,292 --> 00:41:06,125
[Vanessa grunts softly]

695
00:41:09,792 --> 00:41:11,125
Vanessa.

696
00:41:11,625 --> 00:41:12,667
You're here.

697
00:41:12,750 --> 00:41:14,333
Yes, I'm here.

698
00:41:15,708 --> 00:41:17,333
I'm right here.

699
00:41:18,333 --> 00:41:19,958
It's so good to see you.

700
00:41:21,083 --> 00:41:23,333
Why are you acting so strange?

701
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:25,000
Well, I... I...

702
00:41:25,458 --> 00:41:26,583
I didn't think... I...

703
00:41:27,583 --> 00:41:28,667
I didn't think that...

704
00:41:29,292 --> 00:41:31,375
You didn't think what?

705
00:41:35,792 --> 00:41:36,792
I just...

706
00:41:37,167 --> 00:41:38,417
I wasn't... [sobs]

707
00:41:42,250 --> 00:41:44,292
I wasn't sure that I would see you again.

708
00:41:46,542 --> 00:41:48,542
That's absurd. I'm right here.

709
00:41:48,625 --> 00:41:50,333
Yes, of course. Of course you are.

710
00:41:50,625 --> 00:41:52,333
Yes, you are right here. Of course.

711
00:41:57,167 --> 00:41:59,250
What can I do? Can I do something for you?

712
00:41:59,333 --> 00:42:01,708
Are you thirsty?
Can I get you something to drink?

713
00:42:01,792 --> 00:42:03,583
Like water, or...

714
00:42:03,667 --> 00:42:06,125
Or are you hungry?
I can get you something to eat.

715
00:42:06,208 --> 00:42:08,667
Anything. I--
I could get anything you want.

716
00:42:08,750 --> 00:42:09,750
Yes.

717
00:42:09,833 --> 00:42:12,250
I'd like a pineapple juice.

718
00:42:13,083 --> 00:42:14,208
With ice.

719
00:42:16,292 --> 00:42:17,875
You don't like pineapple.

720
00:42:18,375 --> 00:42:19,375
I don't?

721
00:42:19,833 --> 00:42:20,958
No. Your-- Your lips.

722
00:42:21,042 --> 00:42:23,208
It-- It makes them tingle, I believe.

723
00:42:28,167 --> 00:42:29,625
Let's try anyway.

724
00:42:29,708 --> 00:42:30,917
-[Fisk] Mmm-hmm.
-Shall we?

725
00:42:31,333 --> 00:42:32,333
Yeah. Nurse?

726
00:42:32,417 --> 00:42:33,417
Nurse!

727
00:42:33,542 --> 00:42:34,542
[nurse] Is everything okay?

728
00:42:34,625 --> 00:42:36,708
No. I mean, she's awake.

729
00:42:36,792 --> 00:42:39,500
Wait. She wants a pineapple juice.

730
00:42:39,583 --> 00:42:40,833
Sir, I need to--

731
00:42:40,917 --> 00:42:41,917
No!

732
00:42:42,833 --> 00:42:45,542
Pineapple juice in a glass, with ice.

733
00:42:46,708 --> 00:42:48,958
-Wilson.
-Yes?

734
00:42:49,042 --> 00:42:51,042
Why did you scare the poor girl? She--

735
00:42:51,125 --> 00:42:52,125
[Fisk] No.

736
00:42:52,208 --> 00:42:55,167
-You practically made her cry.
-No, I, I just... Um...

737
00:42:55,875 --> 00:42:58,292
I'm just overwhelmed, my love, that's all.

738
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,083
Please.

739
00:43:01,167 --> 00:43:02,667
I've never seen you like this.

740
00:43:03,625 --> 00:43:04,958
I just thought that...

741
00:43:07,333 --> 00:43:09,667
I'm just glad you're with me here again.

742
00:43:09,750 --> 00:43:10,750
That's all.

743
00:43:11,708 --> 00:43:12,708
[Vanessa] But...

744
00:43:12,792 --> 00:43:14,542
why did you think I'd gone?

745
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:16,000
I don't know.

746
00:43:17,333 --> 00:43:18,333
I, uh...

747
00:43:20,083 --> 00:43:21,917
I just missed you so much.

748
00:43:22,375 --> 00:43:24,375
That's all. I just missed you so much.

749
00:43:24,458 --> 00:43:25,833
I missed you, too.

750
00:43:25,917 --> 00:43:28,917
-Yeah?
-I'm so glad to be here with you.

751
00:43:33,042 --> 00:43:34,042
Yes, baby.

752
00:43:46,875 --> 00:43:49,042
Is there something else you need, my dear?

753
00:43:49,917 --> 00:43:50,917
No.

754
00:43:52,417 --> 00:43:53,750
That was divine.

755
00:43:54,417 --> 00:43:55,417
Good.

756
00:43:58,667 --> 00:43:59,667
[Vanessa] Wilson.

757
00:44:00,250 --> 00:44:01,500
Yes, my love.

758
00:44:01,583 --> 00:44:03,167
Will you tell me a story?

759
00:44:05,250 --> 00:44:06,375
A story?

760
00:44:08,042 --> 00:44:09,292
Yes.

761
00:44:09,375 --> 00:44:11,583
A story, please.

762
00:44:13,042 --> 00:44:15,292
What kind of story
would you like me to tell?

763
00:44:16,292 --> 00:44:18,417
Tell me the story of how we met.

764
00:44:20,708 --> 00:44:22,208
Oh.

765
00:44:29,250 --> 00:44:31,958
I've arranged for a more private
showing, but...

766
00:44:32,833 --> 00:44:33,833
this is it.

767
00:44:34,250 --> 00:44:35,417
This is the gallery.

768
00:44:39,167 --> 00:44:42,542
[Vanessa] Somehow, I must have known
that you would walk

769
00:44:42,625 --> 00:44:45,000
through those doors and change everything.

770
00:44:46,333 --> 00:44:48,125
Lucky then, I guess, that day.

771
00:44:48,750 --> 00:44:50,542
Mmm, no.

772
00:44:51,167 --> 00:44:52,167
Not luck.

773
00:44:53,625 --> 00:44:54,750
Not luck at all.

774
00:44:56,542 --> 00:44:58,792
It was the grand design.

775
00:44:58,875 --> 00:45:00,750
-Mmm.
